This paper deals with energy harvesting communication systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves power allocation and transmitter switching policies, which are related to control and systems engineering (cs.SY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the transmission of data, which is related to Multimedia (cs.MM).
